listitem.para:
&clisp; can store and retrieve values of the
    following types:&string-t;
     &vector-t; (meaning anything that can be &coerce;d to
      &ubyte-vec;)
     EXT:32BIT-VECTOR (meaning
      (&vector-t; &ubyte-32;))
     &integer-t;&single-float-t;
     &double-float-t;
    and :DEFAULT-KEY-TYPE
    and :DEFAULT-VALUE-TYPE-TYPE should be one of
    those.  If not specified (or &nil;), the &type-k;
    argument is required in the access functions below.
